import React, {useState, useEffect} from 'react' import '../styling/doctors.css' export default function ViewDoctors(){ const[doctors, setDoctors] = useState([]) const[search, setSearch] = useState('') useEffect(() => { fetch('/doctors') .then(response => response.json()) .then(data => setDoctors(data)) },[]) const allDoctors = doctors.filter(doctor => doctor.name.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase()) || doctor.speciality.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase()) || doctor.location.toLowerCase().includes(search.toLowerCase()) || doctor.contact ) const listDoctors = allDoctors.map((doctor) => { return( {doctor.id} {doctor.name} {doctor.phone} {doctor.speciality} {doctor.location} ) }) return(
setSearch(e.target.value)}/> {listDoctors}
ID. Name Contact Speciality Location
) }
